{
  "texts": [
    "25% of the notes underwent dual annotation.",
    "Before adjudication, dually-annotated notes had a Cohen's kappa coefficient of 0.589, which reflects moderate agreement 36, and highlights the ambiguity and subjectivity of annotating complex concepts such as housing instability.",
    "Because housing status can change over time, it's important to be able to distinguish between current and past housing instability.",
    "This may be especially important for certain groups of patients, such as pregnant women, where housing instability during pregnancy may have different implications than prior housing instability.",
    "2 and 3 and Supplementary Tables S7 and S8 illustrate the differences in performance metrics between GPT-4, GPT-3.5, RegEx and manual annotation in identifying notes related to current or past housing instability, measured against final adjudicated labels."
  ]
}